  "prompt": "What universities does Lakeland Financial recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Lakeland Financial frequently recruits new grads from a variety of universities, focusing on institutions where they can establish strong partnerships and where students are well-trained in relevant disciplines. Commonly targeted universities might include local and regional schools such as Indiana University, Purdue University, and other institutions within Indiana and neighboring states.\n\nThe majors that Lakeland Financial tends to focus on typically align with the financial services and banking industry. These would include:\n\n1. Finance\n2. Accounting\n3. Business Administration\n4. Economics\n5. Marketing\n6. Information Technology \n7. Data Analytics\n\nAdditionally, they may also consider other related fields that provide strong analytical, quantitative, and communication skills. The exact schools and programs can vary and may include a broader range of universities depending on specific needs and strategic initiatives at any given time. If you are interested, it's a good idea to check their career pages or reach out to their HR department for the most current information.",
